Certainly! Below is a basic C++ code snippet that demonstrates how to create a simple program that outputs "Hello, World!" to the console.

```cpp
#include <iostream>

// Entry point of the program
int main() {
    // Output "Hello, World!" to the console
    std::cout << "Hello, World!" << std::endl;
    return 0; // Indicates that the program ended successfully
}
```

This code includes the necessary header file to utilize the input/output stream library, defines the `main` function, and uses `std::cout` to print a string to the console. To run this code, you would need a C++ compiler installed on your system. Please feel free to reach out if you have any specific requirements or further questions.
